Name: Parker - Tutorial Area
TooltipDescription: Tutorial area at the start of the game.

Name: Parker - Safehouse
TooltipDescription: Game starting safehouse. Near ore processing plant.

Name: Parker - Abandoned Safehouse
TooltipDescription: Abandoned red faction safehouse in Parker.

Name: Parker - Sand Sifter Factory
TooltipDescription: Next to an ore collecting funnel and across the road from several large gas tanks.

Name: Parker - Ore Processing Plant
TooltipDescription: A restricted EDF target with two smokestacks and a building. EDF vehicles are usually parked here.

Name: Parker - Mountain
TooltipDescription: On top of a mountain in Dust overlooking the small town of Red Rock.

Name: Dust - Safehouse (North)
TooltipDescription: Near tharsis point wind farm and Dust town hall.

Name: Dust - Safehouse (South)
TooltipDescription: Near chemical plant.

Name: Dust - Quarry
TooltipDescription: Inside the quarry. Includes several storage buildings with explosions and a large mining excavator.

Name: Dust - Town of Dust
TooltipDescription: On a hill overlooking the town of Dust. Has several stores, a bar, a prison, and medical clinic.

Name: Dust - Windfarm
TooltipDescription: The center of the Windfarm in northern Dust. Several windmills and EDF guard towers.

Name: Dust - Town Hall
TooltipDescription: Outside of the EDF controlled Dust Town Hall.

Name: Dust - EDF Executive Housing
TooltipDescription: On a hill overlooking a housing complex used by EDF officers. The area below is restricted.

Name: Dust - Chemical Depot
TooltipDescription: Entrance of the chemical depot in Dust. Has several offices, a workers apartment, and many gas tanks.

Name: Dust - Mohole
TooltipDescription: Next to the small mohole in dust. In a restricted area.

Name: Dust - Mountain
TooltipDescription: Top of a large mountain/ridge in Dust.

Name: Badlands - Safehouse (RF HQ)
TooltipDescription: Main safehouse in Badlands. Also the HQ of the Red Faction.

Name: Badlands - Safehouse (Marauder)
TooltipDescription: Safehouse in marauder territory. Unless you want hostile marauders, wait until you've completed certain missions to go here.

Name: Badlands - EDF Outpost
TooltipDescription: The big one.

Name: Badlands - Mohole
TooltipDescription: Big 'ol hole in the ground used to pull heat from Mars' core for terraforming purposes. There's a smaller one in Dust.

Name: Badlands - Harrington Memorial Bridge
TooltipDescription: The big one.

Name: Badlands - EDF Barracks
TooltipDescription: EDF Barracks sitting in a hilly area south of the EDF airbase in Badlands.

Name: Badlands - Marauder Territory
TooltipDescription: Entrance to a Marauder base.

Name: Badlands - Ultor Ruins
TooltipDescription: Large abandoned Ultor ruins in Marauder territory.

Name: Badlands - Irradiated Zone
TooltipDescription: In the middle of the irradiated zone.

Name: Badlands - Old Coot
TooltipDescription: Old coots shack next to the Mohole.

Name: Badlands - Mars Rover
TooltipDescription: The mars rover easter egg.

Name: Oasis - Safehouse
TooltipDescription: Near EDF vehicle depot.

Name: Oasis - Residential District
TooltipDescription: Residential area of Oasis. Has several apartment buildings and gas stations.

Name: Oasis - Industrial District
TooltipDescription: In the middle of the Industrial District of Oasis. Has several smokestacks and factories.

Name: Oasis - EDF Barracks
TooltipDescription: Outside of an EDF Barracks in Oasis, near the Arc Reactor.

Name: Oasis - Reactor Core
TooltipDescription: On a hillside overlooking the Arc Reactor.

Name: Free Fire Zone - Minor Safehouse
TooltipDescription: Abandoned EDF base in the free fire zone. Manned by guerrilla fighters.

Name: Free Fire Zone - Artillery Border (South)
TooltipDescription: Southern border of the artillery kill zone. Next to the EDF border checkpoint.

Name: Free Fire Zone - Artillery Border (North)
TooltipDescription: Northern border of the artillery kill zone. Next to the bridge.

Name: Free Fire Zone - Artillery Base
TooltipDescription: Base which runs and protects the EDF Artillery Gun. Deadly to be here until the FFZ has been liberated.

Name: Free Fire Zone - Artillery Gun
TooltipDescription: Bottom of the EDF Artillery Gun. Deadly to be here until the FFZ has been liberated.

Name: EOS - Safehouse (West)
TooltipDescription: Near FFZ entrance/exit and Eos Memorial Bridge.

Name: EOS - Safehouse (East)
TooltipDescription: Near construction site.

Name: EOS - South Border
TooltipDescription: Border of EOS and the Free Fire Zone

Name: EOS - Residential District
TooltipDescription: Residential area north of the western EOS safehouse. Has two apartment buildings, two bridges, and a EDF monument.

Name: EOS - Martian Council
TooltipDescription: Martian Council building in northern EOS. The EDF are hostile here.

Name: EOS - Outside EDF Central Command
TooltipDescription: Right outside the defense shield.

Name: EOS - Inside EDF Central Command
TooltipDescription: Right inside past the defense shield.

Name: EOS - EDF Central Command Main Building
TooltipDescription: The final building at the peak of the inner valley / cliffsides.

Name: Mount Vogel - Border
TooltipDescription: Border of Mount Vogel and EOS

Name: Mount Vogel - Base
TooltipDescription: Bottom of Mount Vogel and mass accelerator. Several old buildings.

Name: Mount Vogel - Peak
TooltipDescription: Peak of Mount Vogel with mass accelerator exit.

Name: Map Center (OUT OF BOUNDS)
TooltipDescription: Center of the game map. Out of bounds, so make sure that you have infinite jetpack on so you don't fall through the map.

Name: Dust - Crater Grounds (OUT OF BOUNDS)
TooltipDescription: Area south of dust overlooking the crater grounds. Be careful not to fall out of the map.
